4. Don‚Äôt get discouraged by other people‚Äôs success. The pie is big enough for EVERYONE to win.

My lesson here is this:

1. It‚Äôs okay to take a loss in this market. Get back on your feet, and keep pushing forward.
2. Crypto is advantageous to a long-term mentality winner‚Äôs game. Don‚Äôt think so short -term and don‚Äôt be discouraged when trades go south.
Anyone who claims a 100% win rate in these markets is either lying or not telling the full truth. Even the best traders take L‚Äôs or have some break-even trades.

Admist what sounds like amazing wins, I am not perfect. 

I have winners and I have losers and I don‚Äôt have a 100% success rate, but I do my best to increase the maximum chance of success based on my research thesis at that time.
My portfolio surpassed the $1 Million mark and my NFT portfolio has made me more money now, then when Bitcoin was itching to break $65,000 a year back.

NOBODY can predict what will happen in the market tomorrow and nobody knows 100% guaranteed what will take off next.

What we can do is use our best judgement to make a high probability decision to help us win the most as investors.

Over the past year, we‚Äôve had some massive wins, but that doesn‚Äôt come at the cost of some L‚Äôs as well.

We often times get caught up in just the winners and being on the ‚Äúhot streak‚Äù, but I want people to know, the reality of the situation is...
